<p>To help you understand the importance of data security and privacy, here is a comparison table highlighting the key differences between the two:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><thead><tr><th>Data Security</th><th>Data Privacy</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Focuses on protecting data from unauthorized access and breaches.</td><td>Focuses on controlling how data is collected, used, and shared.</td></tr><tr><td>Involves implementing encryption, access controls, and firewalls.</td><td>Involves establishing consent, anonymization, and data retention policies.</td></tr><tr><td>Ensures data integrity and confidentiality.</td><td>Ensures compliance with regulations and safeguards individual rights.</td></tr><tr><td>Guards against external threats such as hackers and malware.</td><td>Protects against internal misuse or unauthorized disclosure of data.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



